# Security headers for Cloudflare Pages
# These apply when SKIP_STATIC=true on Render (Pages serves the SPA)
#
# CSP notes (2026-05-08, Phase 6 — script-src fully hardened, style-src
# kept permissive due to motion/react runtime <style> injection):
#   * script-src     — `'unsafe-eval'` and `'unsafe-inline'` BOTH dropped.
#                      Production bundle has no eval/new Function.
#                      One class of inline script is allowlisted by
#                      SHA-256 hash:
#                        Vocaband's boot-debug.js — inlined into
#                        index.html by vocabandHtmlPerf (vite.config.ts).
#                        The plugin auto-rewrites the BOOT_DEBUG hash in
#                        dist/_headers at build time from the actual file
#                        contents, so this checked-in value can drift and
#                        still ship a correct policy. The format below
#                        MUST stay a single sha256 token quoted in both
#                        script-src and script-src-elem so the regex
#                        replacement finds it. If this value doesn't
#                        match the source file's current hash, the build
#                        warns but still ships the correct hash to dist.
#                          BOOT_DEBUG (2026-05-28): z5MjfxMPtqtftEDZ5Enyqcs6M/7NvYpUtUbexmB/jrI=
#
#                      (2026-05-23) Cloudflare Insights retired: the
#                      product injected a rotating inline bootstrap
#                      script that forced a per-rotation hash addition
#                      to the CSP (6 rotations in 9 days, PRs #882, #885,
#                      #899, #900, #905 and follow-ups).  Replaced by
#                      Cloudflare Web Analytics, which counts traffic
#                      server-side without injecting any script — no
#                      hash treadmill, no static.cloudflareinsights.com
#                      origin, no cloudflareinsights.com connect-src.
#                      Removed: 5 rotating hashes + the two origins.
#                      Sentry continues to cover client-side error
#                      telemetry.  See docs/operator-tasks.md (closed).
#                      *** This is the high-value XSS-defence win. ***
#   * style-src-elem — `'unsafe-inline'` KEPT. motion/react injects
#                      <style>...</style> blocks at runtime for animation
#                      keyframes (spring/layout/keyframes anims). The content
#                      is dynamic so we can't hash it; nonce-based CSP would
#                      require a Worker template-rewrite. Tracked as deferred
#                      hardening — same risk class as style-src-attr.
#   * style-src-attr — `'unsafe-inline'` KEPT. motion/react writes
#                      transform/opacity to the element's `style` attribute
#                      every frame. CSS-only — cannot escalate to JS.
#   * media-src      — `https://*.r2.dev` ADDED. Production VITE_CLOUDFLARE_URL
#                      points at the R2 public bucket alias
#                      (https://pub-<hash>.r2.dev), which is the same origin
#                      served via the audio.vocaband.com custom domain.
#                      Without it Howler in HTML5 mode (see #676) couldn't
#                      load any word MP3 — every word fell back to browser
#                      TTS and the console screamed CSP violations.
#                      Also added to connect-src for the same reason — some
#                      callers (FreeResourcesView audio-pack download
#                      preview) fetch the MP3 directly.
#
# 2026-05-22 — img-src wildcard removed (ZAP "CSP: Wildcard Directive"):
#   * img-src        — `https:` REMOVED, replaced with explicit allowlist:
#                      challenges.cloudflare.com (Turnstile widget assets),
#                      *.supabase.co (any future image bucket — mirrors the
#                      pattern used by the `sound` bucket), *.r2.dev (future
#                      R2 image hosting — mirrors media-src), and
#                      lh3.googleusercontent.com (Google OAuth avatars from
#                      user_metadata.picture, not rendered today but the
#                      data is there). Audit before this change: no client
#                      code loads <img src="https://..."> from any external
#                      host — all UI images are 'self', data:, or blob:.
#                      If a future feature loads an image from a host not
#                      on this list it will silently fail; add the host
#                      here (don't restore the wildcard).
#
# 2026-05-16, R5 — Sentry observability:
#   * connect-src     — `https://o4511016408514560.ingest.de.sentry.io`
#                       ADDED.  This is the ingest host derived from the
#                       DSN in src/core/sentry.ts.  Without it the browser
#                       SILENTLY blocks every error event the SDK tries to
#                       POST (CSP violations don't surface as user-visible
#                       failures), which is how the previous Sentry setup
#                       was effectively invisible in production.  Changing
#                       the DSN project requires updating this host AND the
#                       FALLBACK_DSN in sentry.ts at the same time.
#   * script-src-elem — `https://browser.sentry-cdn.com` ADDED.  The replay
#                       integration is lazy-loaded from the Sentry CDN
#                       (Sentry.lazyLoadIntegration('replayIntegration'))
#                       so the ~50 KB gzipped replay code doesn't bloat the
#                       entry chunk on weak school Wi-Fi.  The CDN script
#                       is signed with subresource integrity by the SDK
#                       itself; no SHA-256 allowlist needed here.
#   * connect-src     — `https://browser.sentry-cdn.com` ALSO ADDED.  The
#                       Workbox service worker intercepts every `script`
#                       request (CacheFirst handler on script/style
#                       destinations in vite.config.ts) and re-fetches via
#                       the Fetch API to populate the runtime cache.  That
#                       SW-side `fetch()` is governed by `connect-src`, not
#                       `script-src`, so without the host here the replay
#                       script fails to load with "Refused to connect ...
#                       violates connect-src" even though the script tag
#                       itself would have been permitted.  (The same dual-
#                       directive pattern previously applied to
#                       static.cloudflareinsights.com — retired 2026-05-23,
#                       see the script-src note above.)
#
# 2026-05-24 — www host added to connect-src:
#   * connect-src     — `https://www.vocaband.com` + `wss://www.vocaband.com`
#                       ADDED, mirroring the apex `vocaband.com` pair that
#                       directly precedes them.  The Worker 301-redirects
#                       www→apex for HTML navigations (worker/index.ts), but
#                       Cloudflare Workers Assets serves static files (incl.
#                       /sw.js) on the www host WITHOUT invoking the Worker,
#                       so a Workbox service worker can be — and, for anyone
#                       who visited before the www→apex redirect existed,
#                       still is — registered on www.vocaband.com.  That SW
#                       re-fetches the HTML shell via the Fetch API, which is
#                       governed by connect-src (same mechanism as the
#                       sentry-cdn note above), and the policy listed only the
#                       apex host.  Symptom in the wild: opening a www URL
#                       carrying a query string (e.g. the ?lang=he hreflang
#                       alternate Google indexes) died with "Connecting to
#                       'https://www.vocaband.com/index.html' violates …
#                       connect-src", the SW fetch rejected as "Failed to
#                       fetch", and the navigation fell to a browser error
#                       page.  Allowing the www host lets that SW fetch
#                       resolve so the www→apex redirect can complete.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-XSS-Protection: 0
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(self), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=(), magnetometer=(), gyroscope=(), accelerometer=(), interest-cohort=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin-allow-popups
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-site
  X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'sha256-z5MjfxMPtqtftEDZ5Enyqcs6M/7NvYpUtUbexmB/jrI=' https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://browser.sentry-cdn.com; script-src-elem 'self' 'sha256-z5MjfxMPtqtftEDZ5Enyqcs6M/7NvYpUtUbexmB/jrI=' https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://browser.sentry-cdn.com; style-src-elem 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; style-src-attr 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: blob: https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://*.supabase.co https://*.r2.dev https://lh3.googleusercontent.com; connect-src 'self' https://auth.vocaband.com wss://auth.vocaband.com https://api.vocaband.com wss://api.vocaband.com https://vocaband.fly.dev wss://vocaband.fly.dev https://*.supabase.co wss://*.supabase.co https://vocaband.com wss://vocaband.com https://www.vocaband.com wss://www.vocaband.com https://audio.vocaband.com https://*.r2.dev https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://fonts.googleapis.com https://fonts.gstatic.com https://o4511016408514560.ingest.de.sentry.io https://browser.sentry-cdn.com; media-src 'self' https://auth.vocaband.com https://*.supabase.co https://*.cloudflare.com https://audio.vocaband.com https://*.r2.dev; worker-src 'self' blob:; frame-src https://accounts.google.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://accounts.google.com

# Cache static assets aggressively (hashed filenames)
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Never cache the HTML shell — not the literal file, and not the navigable
# routes users actually request. /, /student and /accessibility-statement
# are run_worker_first (wrangler.jsonc), so the Worker serves their HTML;
# without a rule here they inherited Workers Assets' default
# (max-age=0, must-revalidate), which Cloudflare edge-caches. A cached
# shell from a previous deploy then pairs an OLD inlined boot-debug script
# with the CSP applied fresh above, and the browser blocks it as a hash
# mismatch. no-store keeps the shell off the edge + browser cache; the
# Worker stamps the same header (see worker/index.ts noStoreHtml) so the
# two layers agree. Hashed /assets/* stay immutable above.
/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-store, must-revalidate
/
  Cache-Control: no-store, must-revalidate
/student
  Cache-Control: no-store, must-revalidate
/accessibility-statement
  Cache-Control: no-store, must-revalidate

# Don't cache service worker
/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate

# PWA manifest: short TTL so theme/icon/name edits propagate within a
# deploy cycle (it's not under /assets/, so the immutable rule above
# doesn't catch it; without this header CF's default would cache for
# hours and installed PWAs wouldn't pick up changes promptly).
/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate

# PDFs are regenerated by scripts/teacher-pdfs/build.mjs and
# scripts/presentation-pdf/build.mjs — not content-hashed, so we can't
# cache them forever, but a short cache + revalidate balances speed
# with the ability to ship a typo fix without making teachers wait.
# Explicit Content-Type defends against any future Worker layer that
# might sniff the body and mislabel a non-rendered response.
/Vocaband-Presentation-HE.pdf
  Content-Type: application/pdf
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
/Vocaband-Presentation-AR.pdf
  Content-Type: application/pdf
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
/docs/*.pdf
  Content-Type: application/pdf
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
